<div class="post">
                        <div class="postTitle">
                            <h2> Margaritas on my Mind</h2>
                            <h5 class="date">27 July 2016</h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="postContent">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    I don’t always drink Tequila…But when I do, it’s in a margarita. Fruity margaritas, to spicy margaritas, on the rocks, or frozen, the summer sun puts me in a margarita mindset. Here is a list of some of the greatest margarita recipes for your next get together. My favorite is a combo of the fruity and spicy margarita. In Belmar, New Jersey at the 10th Ave. Burrito they have a Spicy Pineapple Margarita with El Jimador Reposado, Pineapple, Habanero, Lime, and cane sugar. One of my favorites!
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <br>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h3 class="date">Mint Julep Margarita</h3>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-5">
                                    <h4>Ingredients:</h4> 2 limes
                                    <br> 2 tsp. superfine sugar
                                    <br> 10 fresh mint leaves
                                    <br> 2 oz. bourbon
                                    <br> 1 oz. orange liqueur
                                    <br> ¼ C. Seltzer
                                    <br>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-7">
                                    <img src="/img/julepMarg.png" width="100%">
                                    <div class="copyright text-right">image by thedish.restaurant.com</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h4>Directions:</h4> Place cut up limes, sugar, and mint leaves in cocktail shaker to muddle. Add the bourbon, orange liquor and a couple ice cubes. Shake well and strain into glass. Can be served over ice or straight. Top with seltzer and garnish with a lime wedge.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <br>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h3 class="date">Chile-Agave Margarita</h3>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-7">
                                    <img src="/img/chiliMarg.png" width="100%">
                                    <div class="copyright text-right">image by rachaelrayshow.com</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-5">
                                    <h4>Ingredients:</h4> 1 Tbsp. turbinado sugar
                                    <br>1 tsp orange rind
                                    <br>1/8 tsp kosher salt
                                    <br>8 thin slices of chile
                                    <br>2 Tbsp. lime juice 1 Tbsp. fresh orange juice
                                    <br>1 Tbsp. light agave nectar
                                    <br>2 oz. anejo tequila
                                    <br>1 oz. Grand Marnier
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h4>Directions:</h4> Combine the sugar, orange rind, and salt on a plate. Moisten rims and dip rims in plate to coat. Place 4 chile slices in shaker to muddle. Add remaining ingredients and fill shaker with ice. Strain into prepared glasses, and add chile slices for garnish.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <br>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h3 class="date">Watermelon Margarita</h3>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-5">
                                    <h4>Ingredients:</h4> 2 tsp sugar
                                    <br> 1 lime wedge
                                    <br> 3 ½ C. cubed seeded watermelon
                                    <br> ½ C. tequila
                                    <br> 2 Tbsp. Sugar
                                    <br> 3 Tbsp. lime juice
                                    <br> 1 Tbsp. Triple Sec
                                    <br> Lime wedges or watermelon balls
                                    <br>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-7">
                                    <img src="/img/waterMarg.png" width="100%">
                                    <div class="copyright text-right">image by sagerecipes.com</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h4>Directions:</h4> Rub rims of 6 glasses with a lime wedge and rub the rims in the 2 Tbsp. of sugar. Combine the watermelon, tequila, sugar, lime juice, and triple sec in a blender. Blend till smooth. Fill glasses with crushed ice and add margarita. Garnish with lime wedges and melon balls.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <br>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h3 class="date">Prickly Pear Margarita</h3>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-7">
                                    <img src="/img/pearMarg.png" width="100%">
                                    <div class="copyright text-right">image by flipmyfood.com</div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-5">
                                    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>1 lime wedge
                                    <br> 3 C. fresh lime juice
                                    <br> 3 C. Silver Tequila
                                    <br> 2 C. prickly pear syrup
                                    <br> 1 C. orange liqueur
                                    <br> Coarse pink salt for rimming glasses
                                    <br>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h4>Directions:</h4> Place the pink salt in a plate and rim glasses with it using a lime wedge. Fill a pitcher with ice and add lime juice, tequila, prickly pear syrup, and orange liqueur. Stir together and strain into glasses. Makes 10 cocktails.
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <br>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h3 class="date">French Margarita</h3>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-5">
                                    <h4>Ingredients:</h4> 2 oz. tequila
                                    <br> 1 oz. Grand Marnier
                                    <br> ½ oz. of lime juice, orange juice, and sweet and sour mix
                                    <br> 1 oz. Chambord
                                    <br> Garnish with berries
                                    <br>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-7">
                                    <img src="/img/frenchMarg.png" width="100%">
                                    <div class="copyright text-right">image by thellosonoma.com</div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-12">
                                    <h4>Directions:</h4> Pour tequila, Grand Marnier, lime juice, orange juice, and sour mix into a shaker and shake to mix. Fill a margarita glass with ice and strain the mixture into the glass. Top with Chambord and garnish with a skewer of berries.
                                </div>
                            </div>
